column2: If you solder a log pot (A) for LEVEL you don´t need to solder RL1 and RL2. In other words, if you can´t find log pots for Level, you can solder RL1 and RL2 for a fake log response on a linear potentiometer.
You don´t need to mount nuts for PAN and EQ

The send channels can be set to be active either pre or post AFL per channel via a solder bridge. ‚Pre‘ means you can still hear the send/return way when it is in AFL mode (thus the channels signal is actually not audible in the main mix), ‚post‘ means send/return will only work when the channels signal is routed to the main mix.
On V2 PCBs there is a capacitor without a part name, that is C52.
